hopobject.body: I'd like to tell you about a change of address cyclogyl prix Alfa has acheived 215bhp/tonne with the 4C's Â 237bhp 1.7-litre turbocharged engine, meaning a 0-62mph sprint time of 5.0 seconds and a top speed of 160mph. The engine is mated to the latest generation of Alfa's dry twin-clutch transmission. Up to 80 per cent of the car's 258lb/ft of torque is available from 1800rpm, something that Alfa says underlines the flexible nature of the new engine. Rumours still persist that a V6-engined option will also become available in the future. Alfa's DNA driver select system is also incorporated, and now also features a new 'race' mode.
